<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIOLENCE IN JERUSALEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As I read your report (Part A, Oct. 8) on the Bush Administration's go-ahead 
for a $400-million loan to construct housing for Soviet Jews in Israel, I 
looked up at the TV screen and watched Israeli troops gunning down fleeing 
Palestinian youths and barring ambulance crews from picking up wounded 
Palestinians. 
</P>
<P>
Why is it the Israelis can shoot into civilian crowds, beat old people, 
children, women, imprison men without due cause, blow up the homes of relatives 
of suspected Palestinians -- in other words, trample on every right we hold 
dear -- and our Congress continues to reward them with more aid? It is time 
this aid be stopped. 
</P>
<P>
PATRICIA McDONNELL 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, ..., KAL / BALTIMORE SUN 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
