<HEADLINE>
<P>
JURY VERDICTS IN CINCINNATI, FT. LAUDERDALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Look out, Times, your bias is showing again! In "Verdict Is Guilty in 2 Live 
Crew's Rap Album Sale" (Oct. 4) we read that an "all-white" jury convicted 
Charles Freeman of selling obscenity in Florida. 
</P>
<P>
Are you trying to make this anti-obscenity issue into one of race? Simply 
stated, a jury convicted Freeman based on the facts: The lyrics of the songs 
from 2 Live Crew are obscene. Under the guise of "freedom of expression," 2 
Live Crew is hiding words that degrade and violate women and children. The 
music is not the problem, but the words definitely "appeal to a morbid interest 
in sex." I congratulate the jury. 
</P>
<P>
SANDRA SKELLY 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
</TEXT>
