<HEADLINE>
<P>
HATE COVERAGE, MASCOT, BUT LOVE BOB MILLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The consistent superstar for the Kings over the years has been play-by-play man 
Bob Miller. He is the equal of Vin Scully in baseball and Chick Hearn in 
basketball, but now radio listeners are deprived of his voice. 
</P>
<P>
Now that the Kings finally have a single radio station that can be heard 
throughout Southern California, they need to return their greatest asset to the 
listeners. 
</P>
<P>
MARK S. KORNFELD 
</P>
<P>
Crestline 
</P>
</TEXT>
