<HEADLINE>
<P>
DODGERS SHOULD KEEP VALENZUELA, DANIELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1982 when I was 17 and a senior at Garfield High, Fernando Valenzuela came 
out to speak to us. He was a big star then. 
</P>
<P>
He didn't have to come out to see us, but he did. 
</P>
<P>
He told us -- both in Spanish and through an English interpreter -- to stay in 
school. He said any of us could have something he didn't have a chance to have 
-- an education. 
</P>
<P>
I never forgot Fernando's message. I went to school -- Cal State L.A. and then 
got a master's degree from UCLA -- and live a good life with my wife and 
2-year-old son. 
</P>
<P>
I feel as if the tables have been turned. Now my career is going well and 
Fernando needs someone to believe in him. I sincerely hope the Dodgers bring 
Fernando back. I want my Miguelito to see this man. 
</P>
<P>
CARLOS RAMIREZ 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
