<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA'S YOUNG SHOULD HAVE ACTED HIS AGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The televised picture of UCLA Chancellor Charles Young running along the 
sideline and ranting at the officials during last Saturday's football game with 
Arizona defined his mission and his campus more clearly than all the publicity 
releases and promotional films that the school can ever issue. The list of 
great university educators now includes Woody Hayes, Bob Knight, Bo 
Schembechler, Barry Switzer, Jerry Tarkanian and Charles Young. 
</P>
<P>
RONALD L. BAUER 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
