<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPPORTUNISTIC SUNNY HILLS ROUTS BUENA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS KAISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENA PARK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sunny Hills, turning two interceptions and a fumble recovery into touchdowns, 
defeated Buena Park, 33-0, Friday in the teams' Freeway League opener. 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park (2-4) fell behind, 7-0, with 4:38 left in the first quarter when 
Sunny Hills' Joey Montgomery intercepted a pass by quarterback Mark Medellin 
and returned it 45 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
The Lancers' second touchdown by interception was a 69-yard return by lineman 
Jeff Hicks with 1:10 remaining in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
A third touchdown by Sunny Hills' defense came with 4:22 remaining in the game 
after a Coyotes' flea-flicker play failed. Buena Park reserve quarterback Geno 
Robles completed a five-yard pass to Juan Guerra, but Guerra's lateral was 
grabbed by Brent Howes, who ran 60 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills' other two touchdowns were scored by the offense. Quarterback 
Hakeim McKenzie scored on a six-yard keeper with 7:23 remaining in the third 
quarter and Mike Sullivan scored three minutes later on a 45-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
Sullivan rushed for 93 yards in nine carries for Sunny Hills (3-3). DENNIS 
KAISER 
</P>
</TEXT>
