<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANYON'S DEFENSE STYMIES FOOTHILL FOR A 12-3 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TUSTIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canyon's Darren Lish threw a pair of second-half touchdown passes to George 
Garcia to lead the Comanches to a 12-3 victory over Foothill in the Century 
League opener for both teams Friday at Tustin High School. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon's offense sputtered in the first half, gaining only three first downs 
and committing three turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
But the Comanche defense held Foothill scoreless until it surrendered a 26-yard 
field goal by Keo Powell with 33 seconds left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
"I told our kids that everything that could have gone wrong for us in the first 
half did go wrong and we were only down three," Canyon Coach Loren Shumer said. 
</P>
<P>
And the offense did get it together. Canyon (3-3 overall, 1-0 in league), after 
forcing Foothill (1-5, 0-1) to punt, took the ball at the Knights' 37. Lish hit 
Jeff Brunswig for a 54-yard completion that set up a Canyon first-and-goal at 
the nine. A holding play pushed the ball back to the 19, but two plays later 
Lish threw 16 yards to Garcia for the score. Greg Lawrence's extra-point 
attempt hit the crossbar and bounced back, making the score 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
The Canyon defense forced another Foothill punt, giving the Comanches the ball 
at their own 41. Brunswig did most of the work for Canyon as he carried four 
times for 39 yards on the nine-play drive. Garcia capped it when he caught a 
21-yard pass from Lish. JOE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
