<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRVINE TAKES TO AIR, BEATS DANA HILLS, 26-14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DANA POINT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Junior quarterback Jason Minici passed for 304 yards and two touchdowns to lead 
Irvine High School to a 26-14 victory over Dana Hills in a South Coast League 
opener Friday night at Dana Hills High. 
</P>
<P>
Minici threw touchdown passes of 25 and 55 yards as Irvine (5-1) came back from 
a 7-6 second-quarter deficit for the victory in front of 4,500. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine running back Scott Seal added a touchdown on a 10-yard run and was the 
game's leading rusher with 125 yards in 24 carries. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills (3-2-1) was led by quarterback Albie Sukut, who passed for 167 yards 
and ran for a 15-yard touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Huffman and Chris Perry each caught a touchdown pass from Minici. After 
Dana Hills jumped out to a 7-6 lead in the second quarter, Minici threw a 
24-yard touchdown pass to Perry to make it 12-7 at the half. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine then scored the clinching touchdown on a 55-yard pass from Minici to 
Huffman with 9:56 left in the third quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
