<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UCI WATER POLO GIVES NEWLAND HIS 499TH COACHING VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pablo Yrizar had four goals to lead the UC Irvine water polo team to a 13-4 
victory over UC San Diego in a nonconference water polo game Friday at Heritage 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine Coach Ted Newland is one victory shy of the 500th of his college 
coaching career. 
</P>
<P>
His record is 499-175-5. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine (9-8), the eighth-ranked team in the nation, built a 7-0 halftime lead 
and had an 8-0 lead before San Diego scored with 1 minute 57 seconds remaining 
in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine's Jay Warren added two goals. Yrizar has 52 goals this season. 
</P>
<P>
In Big West conference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Nevada Las Vegas 2, UC Irvine 0 -- UC Irvine (4-10-1, 0-1 in conference) lost 
its Big West Conference opener Friday in Las Vegas. The Rebels (6-5-2, 3-2) got 
goals from Terry Pryer and Doug Borgel. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 2, UC Santa Barbara 1 -- T.C. Valentine and Bryan Lou 
scored for host Cal State Fullerton (5-5-3, 3-2) Friday. Santa Barbara (7-4, 
3-1) scored on Kendal Fargo's goal. 
</P>
<P>
In the Cal State Fullerton women's volleyball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 3, U.S. International 0 -- Freshman Becky Howlett had 20 
kills as host Cal State Fullerton (4-18) stopped a 14-match losing streak with 
a 15-13, 15-8, 15-11 victory in the round-robin tournament. In another 
tournament game, William &amp; Mary defeated Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, 16-14, 
15-11, 15-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
