<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: NATIONAL HARDCOURT EVENT SCHEDULED AT WESTLAKE CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 150 players will compete in the U. S. Tennis Assn. National men's 
50-55 hardcourt championships beginning Monday at Westlake Tennis and Swim Club 
in Westlake Village. 
</P>
<P>
The tournament, which is open to the public at no charge, starts Monday at 1:30 
p.m. and will continue through Oct. 21. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded players in the age 50-and-older singles division include Len Saputo 
(Walnut Creek, Calif.), Bob Duesler (Newport Beach) and David Weber (Omaha). 
Top-seeded players in the age 55-and-older division are Gordon Davis (Encino), 
Paul Cranis (Boca Raton, Fla.) and Leonard Lindborg (South Laguna). 
</P>
<P>
Pancho Gonzales and Alex Olmedo are featured in the 50-and-older doubles 
division and are seeded seventh. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 818-889-6164. 
</P>
<P>
The San Fernando Valley chapter of the National Football Foundation announced 
that high school football standouts Ron Adelman (Calabasas), Eric Arciniega 
(Burroughs), Tony Cesta (Bell-Jeff) and Jay Sumner (Burbank) have been selected 
players of the week by the coaches at their respective schools. 
</P>
<P>
Each week, the foundation chooses a different group of schools from the 51 in 
the chapter's area, and coaches select their team's best player. Each school in 
the San Fernando Valley area will have a player honored by season's end. 
</P>
<P>
The Valley chapter will hold an open-house meeting Oct. 25 at 6 p.m. at 16235 
Barneston St., Granada Hills. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting is open to anyone interested in high school football. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 818-249-0131. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Maccabee Athletic Club boys' basketball team, made up of 15- to 
16-year-olds, will play the North Hollywood Youth All-Stars on Tuesday at 6:30 
p.m. at the Forum before the Lakers' game against Maccabi Tel Aviv. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 818-784-1958. 
</P>
