<P>
BIRMINGHAM RALLY DOOMS N. HOLLYWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TODD JACOBSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Birmingham High scored 29 unanswered points to come back from a 15-point 
deficit and hand North Hollywood a 35-23 defeat in a Valley Pac-8 Conference 
game Friday night at North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham quarterback Vince Lampkin completed eight of 19 passes for 135 yards 
and a touchdown, and rushed for 56 yards in 16 carries and scored twice. 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood (2-2, 1-1 in league play) scored on its first possession when 
Krikor Kerkonian raced 30 yards for a touchdown. He later intercepted a Lampkin 
pass and returned it 37 yards for a touchdown to give North Hollywood a 21-6 
lead midway through the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham (3-1, 2-0) tied the score, 21-21, midway through the third period 
when Lampkin scored on a three-yard run to cap an eight-play, 66-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood's Leon Gable rushed for 142 yards in 29 carries but did not 
score a touchdown. TODD JACOBSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
