<HEADLINE>
<P>
SWEET NARROWS COLLEGE BASKETBALL CHOICES TO 5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
North Hollywood High basketball standout Jacinda Sweet has narrowed to five her 
list of Division I schools with which she is considering signing a letter of 
intent, according to Coach Rich Allen. 
</P>
<P>
Sweet will take recruiting trips on five successive weekends, beginning this 
Saturday with Arizona. Allen said that Sweet also is considering Washington, 
Cal, Oregon State and defending NCAA champion Stanford. 
</P>
<P>
Sweet averaged 23.4 points, 12.3 rebounds and 4.5 assists a game for the 
Huskies in 1989-90. 
</P>
<P>
The 5-foot-9 senior guard might sign a letter of intent Nov. 14, the first day 
of the NCAA early-signing period. 
</P>
<P>
"She'll definitely sign early," Allen said. "It's sort of driving her crazy." 
STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</TEXT>
