<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aluminum Co. of America: Alcoa said third-quarter profit declined nearly 43% to 
$125 million on revenue of $2.7 billion, which was off 5.6% from 1989. The 
Pittsburgh-based aluminum company said the figures reflect lower earnings from 
its Brazilian operations, a decrease in orders for some fabricated products, 
lower aluminum prices and unfavorable currency-exchange adjustments of $10.9 
million. 
