<P>
BLACKS IN 'STREETCAR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I want to thank Loynd for his observation that the setting is 1947, blue-collar 
New Orleans and that the Hubbles are definitely written as white. 
</P>
<P>
I had the misfortune to see a production of the same play in which Stanley was 
cast as black! I even saw a production of "Henry V" in which Hal (the English 
prince turned king) was played by a black man! We might as well play "A Raisin 
in the Sun" with whites. 
</P>
<P>
SHARON NOBLE 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 
</P>
