<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MURDER CHARGES FILED IN SLAYING OF AIRMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Murder charges have been filed against a reputed gang member who was arrested 
in the slaying of a serviceman after photos taken of the suspect by a hidden 
security camera were broadcast on the news, prosecutors said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Rickey Moore, 18, was to be arraigned in Torrance Municipal Court on Wednesday 
on one count of murder, three counts of attempted murder and one count of 
shooting into an occupied motor vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors said Moore killed Darrell Webb, 20, an Air Force airman, after the 
victim whistled at the defendant's girlfriend at the South Bay Bowling alley in 
Torrance on Sept. 19. 
</P>
<P>
Webb and three of his friends then drove away, but were followed by Moore and 
his girlfriend. When the two cars pulled up to a light, Moore fatally shot Webb 
in the chest, prosecutors said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
