<HEADLINE>
<P>
THIS READER DISAGREES WITH ASSESSMENT OF SEAU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding Robert W. Rae's slanderous remarks about Junior Seau (Oct. 6): I 
talked with Junior when he was in our restaurant just last week. 
</P>
<P>
He is the nicest, most courteous man I have ever met. Even though he was having 
dinner, he took the time to talk with everyone who wanted to talk to him. He 
was quiet, sincere and a pleasure to be around. If Junior is "the biggest jerk" 
or "idiot loudmouth," I'm Saddam Hussein! 
</P>
<P>
As far as his linebacking skills, an oak tree does not grow in a day. Give him 
time. He will be a great one. 
</P>
<P>
CHRISTOPHER B. PIPER 
</P>
<P>
Oceanside 
