<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
2 PLEAD NOT GUILTY TO ANIMAL NEGLECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alfred (Dale) Beem and his son, Robert, pleaded not guilty to misdemeanor 
animal-neglect charges during their arraignment Friday in Ventura Municipal 
Court. 
</P>
<P>
A trial is scheduled for Nov. 14. 
</P>
<P>
The two men were originally charged with felony animal abuse when seven horses, 
69 rabbits and 35 sheep were impounded from their rented ranch on Piru Canyon 
Road in an unincorporated section of the county May 31. Deputy Dist. Atty. Mark 
Pachowicz said the charge was reduced to a misdemeanor due to extenuating 
circumstances, including the fact that the two men had to care for the animals 
alone after Beem's wife and his younger son Michael left Piru to care for 
ailing relatives. 
</P>
<P>
The reduced charge does not lessen the severity of neglect to the animals. 
JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
</TEXT>
