<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY FUROR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am furious. We vote for a large increase in our gasoline taxes and then find 
that we in Ventura County are at the bottom of the list. 
</P>
<P>
The Santa Paula Freeway is one of the most dangerous roads in the state, yet we 
are told that "action can not be taken overnight on something like this." Where 
have these state transportation commissioners been for the last 10 to 15 years 
when people have been killed on this road? 
</P>
<P>
The freeway could be widened for a fraction of the cost of some of these 
freeway projects, but I have a feeling the commissioners have tunnel vision. 
They only see what they want to see. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM LANGLEY 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard 
</P>
</TEXT>
