<P>
5.0 QUAKE RATTLES IRAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A dawn earthquake with a magnitude of 5.0 jolted Zahedan, near Iran's border 
with Pakistan and Afghanistan, on Friday, Tehran Radio said. The quake, the 
fourth to shake the area in two weeks, caused no casualties or damage, the 
