<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEARCH BEGUN FOR AIRCRAFT MISSING OVER ARCTIC OCEAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANCHORAGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A wildlife research plane has disappeared over the Arctic Ocean and a search 
was started Friday over the forbidding polar ice north of Alaska, federal 
officials reported. 
</P>
<P>
The chartered U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service airplane disappeared 280 miles 
northwest of Point Barrow, an agency spokesman said. Point Barrow is the 
northernmost point of land in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
The plane, carrying a pilot and two polar bear specialists from the Fish and 
Wildlife Service, was to have returned Thursday to Prudhoe Bay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
