<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
ESTABLISHMENTS WIN ART DISPLAY AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sculptures and restored antique pictures of downtown Anaheim in foyers and art 
collections displayed throughout the workplace earned awards for three Anaheim 
businesses and a church this week. 
</P>
<P>
The Anaheim campus of FHP Inc., the Anaheim Hilton and Towers, Household Bank 
of Anaheim and the Anaheim United Methodist Church received Art in Public 
Places awards this week. 
</P>
<P>
The Anaheim Arts Council cited the church for its imported, copper wall-like 
sculpture as part of its second annual recognition of art used as part of the 
environment. 
</P>
<P>
Those honored "have installed art because they see a value in this for their 
clients," said Julie Mayer, an artist who chairs the Art in Public Places 
committee. 
</P>
<P>
The council also gave out three so-called chairman's awards. The honors went to 
Multi Vision cable for itscoverage of events in the Anaheim art community, and 
artists Emigdio Vasquez, who has painted and helped restore numerous outdoor 
murals in the city, and Joan Farr, whose large fabric wall hangings drape the 
walls of the Anaheim United Methodist Church. LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</TEXT>
