<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN WANTED ON DRUG CHARGES IS ARRESTED AT MOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 29-year-old man wanted by North Carolina authorities on drug charges was 
arrested Friday as he walked out of a Costa Mesa motel room, FBI officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Todd Christopher Lynch of Charlotte, N.C., was indicted June 6 by a federal 
grand jury on a charge of conspiracy to distribute in excess of 5 kilograms of 
cocaine, FBI spokesman Wylie B. Cox said. 
</P>
<P>
He said Lynch apparently learned of the impending grand jury indictment and 
fled North Carolina before it was handed down. 
</P>
<P>
Cox declined to say how authorities learned of Lynch's presence in Costa Mesa. 
The investigation was conducted by FBI agents and officers with North 
Carolina's Charlotte and Mecklenberg County police departments. 
</P>
<P>
Lynch was arrested without incident at an undisclosed motel on Newport 
Boulevard, Cox said. However, a 9-millimeter semiautomatic handgun "was within 
his reach," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
