</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gun owners who celebrate New Year's Eve by firing their weapons were targeted 
by Los Angeles City Councilwoman Joan Milke Flores Friday for a public 
awareness program aimed at keeping the weapons silent. 
</P>
<P>
Flores introduced a motion calling on the City Council to approve a program to 
inform would-be celebrants just how dangerous it is to fire guns blindly into 
the sky. 
