<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ROCKWELL FINED $42,000 FOR RADIOACTIVE 
SHIPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rockwell International will pay a $42,000 penalty for shipping an excessively 
radioactive container by truck from its Santa Susana Field Laboratory west of 
Chatsworth to Pennsylvania last October, the U.S. Department of Transportation 
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The penalty "is one of the larger" fines assessed in the 15-year history of the 
Hazardous Materials Transportation Act, said Ed Bonekemper, assistant chief 
counsel for the department's research and special programs administration. 
</P>
<P>
The truck was hauling six containers of contaminated equipment from Rockwell 
back to their owners. The violation came to light only because the truck 
blundered into an overpass when the driver got lost on a country road a few 
miles from his destination in Wampum, Pa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
